You are a math expert. When you respond, respond only with the Solution of the final Problem, thinking step by step. At the end of the Solution, when you give your final answer, write it in the form 'Final Answer: \\boxed{$answer$}. I hope it is correct.'
Find all real numbers $x$ such that $\left(\dfrac{x}{3}\right)^3-3x^2+81x-729=25+2(5)(3)+9.$
inference:
$$\left(\dfrac{x}{3}\right)^3-3x^2+81x-729=34$$

$$\dfrac{x^3}{27}-3x^2+81x-755=0$$

$$x^3-27x^2+2187x-20415=0$$

$$(x-3)(x^2-3x-6805)=0$$

$$x=3\quad\text{or}\quad x=\dfrac{3\pm\sqrt{3^2-4(1)(-6805)}}{2(1)}$$

$$x=3\quad\text{or}\quad x=\dfrac{3\pm\sqrt{27221}}{2}$$

$$x=3\quad\text{or}\quad x=\dfrac{3\pm161.75}{2}$$

$$x=3\quad\text{or}\quad x\approx164.75\quad\text{or}\quad x\approx-80.75$$

$$\text{Final Answer: }\boxed{x=-80.75, 3, and 164.75}. \ \text{I hope it is correct.}$$
ground_truth: Both sides of this equation can be simplified using the Binomial Theorem. Note that $-729=(-9)^3$, $25=5^2$, and $9=3^2$. This gives us $\left(\dfrac{x}{3}-9\right)^3=(5+3)^2=8^2=64$, so $\dfrac{x}{3}-9=4$. Therefore, $x=3(4+9)=\boxed{39}$.
